{
  "text": "A dipole appears in the composite corresponding to PC 1 (Fig. 14a) . A positive center over Portugal indicates that the increase in the precipitation associated with PC 1 is also related with an increase in the baroclinic activity . Also, a negative elongated region extending from Iceland, to Scandinavia, to a maximum (negative) on Russia and down to the Suez Canal over land is apparent. The baroclinic activity is reduced over these areas during high PC 1 situations. This is a result traditionally associated with the NAO/Arctic Oscillation (NAO/AO) [CITATION_1] .",
